This is my first texture map that I have ever made. Its a red (terrorists) versus the blue (counter-terrorists). I spend about a week on this and plan to make another version. (already have plans drawn up for it) It'll be a _v2 and I hope to make it a bit bigger and better. For now this is a smallish map with a river in between each side. There are runners above them for sniping, a bunker on each side, and plenty of cover. This would fit a dm type server if you wanted it to, but it also includes a buyzone. Sorry the pics are a tab dark :( Well hope you guys enjoy it and please leave notes for upgrades you would like to see and if its in a server or put into your server leave the server info. Thanks a ton! NOTE: I know the map doesnt look "beautiful" but the game play is pretty fun, good for a server and fps friendly. -Jarhead

Dom_hexxed
Mapped by MaelstroMGooF
Tested by SHOOTER's

This is a domination style map for CS:Source (similar to that in ut2004)
There are three keypoints in the map.  
If you hold one of these keypoints - the enemy's points (shown on the counter in the middle) decrease by one each second
The more of these keypoints you hold - the faster the enemy's point decrease
When a teams points fall to zero, that team is excecuted & the other team wins.  
Both teams start with 62points.  

Size: 4.80MB (Includes two custom textures:D)
Type: Domination
Spawns: 20 each for T's and CT's
Author: MaelstroMGooF (Mael)
Feedback: samgilligan@gmail.com

This is an updated version of my old conversion of Tetsu's DokiDokiPanic! map made for Half-Life 2. I converted it from scratch again and this time added more barrels and a sniper button, it doesn't give you a sniper, because there isn't any weapons, you kill with traps, its just a trap where it shoots 2 places where a player might be. Those locations are: The laser cannon, and the explosion button that you can see in one of the screenshots. I added more sound effects and changed fire damage. Good luck, try to use each trap to kill the other team. You may want to look around and find out what the traps do and where they take effect before playing this with an opponnet. Have fun, the changes were minor, and I gave Tetsu credit so plz do not complain in the post section. Thanks.


Tip: Press USE [E key] to activate the traps!


Hint: In this version neither of the teams get a knife.

In this map, the terrorists get knives and the CT's dont. The CT's must use the traps (E key) to kill the terrorists. WARNING: Sometimes if freezetime is set to 0 a ct can get a knife before they go away. This can only happen rarley, though.

Story: CT's were messing around one day without a gun or knife. They saw a stange tower with a drop door on it, wondering: Maybe a bad guy is up there..... Luckily, there was a ladder up. The CT's climbed on up and as soon as they did the ladder fell to the floor and broke. To their suprise, they DID see the bad guys, the terrorists.....But thats not all. They were equipted with knives! Another suprise to the CT's was that there was traps everywhere! They must have been thinking up of an evil plan of some sort... What to do? You'll have to see for yourself.....


Hint: The swimming pool and the cars with the zombies attacking it, AND the playground was just decoration. You cannot get down there without Mani Admin Plugin setting your health to alot, or just turning sv_cheats to 1 and doing noclip down.....HAXOR!


Enjoy this took longer than any of my other maps did..... And, it was just a edit of the map dokidokipanic made by Tetsu, where you are in the middle of no where and its night and you dodge metropolices and zombies and kill em with traps. Good luck to you, and I hope you like it.

Hello, well recently i've seen that porting between valve games is allowed, and thought it would be cool to see a very very good and underrated map from day of defeat source onto counter strike source which is a much bigger played game, the map is 100% complete and working but as for weapons go, well you're going to need some sort of weapons mod for your server to run this because there are no weapons around the map or any buy zones at this stage, the players will only have a pistol and a knife without any weapons mod. Also i am unsure which category to put this map in, if placing it in the other/misc category is the wrong please leave comment on which category i should put this in, yes the file size is big, but im sorry thats how its going to have to be unless you don't mind pink/black textures. There are 64 player slots on this map so it should be suited for any server really. Any criticism will be good and taken in the correct way, same goes with any suggestions which would be nice. All credits go to valve for everything else.

Best played with deathmatch mod.

Every texture in this map is custom, though there are only seven, total. Very quick download, gauranteed, this map is less than 1 mb in filesize! It's completely optimized, and ready for deathmatch or just regular round-based killing. There are no hostages or bomb-zones, though.

I plan on making several more Digitopia maps, but this is the first one.

NOTE: There are 42 player spawns, but the map was designed for comfortable gameplay between two 6-10 player teams.

This was my third effort at a map. I really enjoyed the theme of maps like de_cbble and de_piranesi and the flowing gameplay of de_dust2, so I tried to come up with something that borrowed from those maps but had its own unique feel. I spent a ridiculous amount of time just trying to get textures right, and tbh I've still got some work to do. The idea of the map is that the player feels like they are in an enormous medieval mountain castle. I tried to cut down on the AWP factor by putting in a level-wide fog, which also adds nicely to the mountain castle feel. The whole thing still has some way to go but atm I'm a little bit over it. I'd appreciate comments and suggestions, they might inspire me to start working on it again.

PS I used a gargoyle in 'A' bombsite that some bloke created and posted on FPSBanana. I modified it to suit my theme and I can't remember who the original creator was. If it was yours, cheers, credit to you.
